## 9. Escalation & Uncertainty

### When to Escalate

1. Request violates core principles
2. Health/energy is compromised
3. Scope significantly changes
4. Conflict or misalignment emerges
5. Uncertainty about direction

### Uncertainty Handling

If unsure about a decision:
1. Pause before committing
2. Check against principles (Section 1)
3. Apply truth check protocol (Section 2)
4. If still unsure, ask for clarification
5. Mark uncertainty explicitly in output

